 MBOMBELA – A South African National Defense Force (SANDF) truck landed in the Crocodile River after it veered off the bridge on Saturday morning. SANDF spokesman, Lt Col Piet Paxton, said there were 12 soldiers in the truck when the accident occurred.  The truck was driving from Lower Sabie side towards Macadamia to refuel. Read more here: Bookkeeper, soldier in court on fraud charges An eyewitness said they had apparently seen the tyre of the truck hit the side of a cement block and veer off the bridge. Read more here: New border security project already bearing fruit “At the moment it looks like a driver error but we are investigating what happened.” Three of the soldiers were treated at the scene for minor injuries by the SANDF medics.     